.TH "recover_context" 9 "recover_context" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
recover_context \- recovers a context in error
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" recover_context
.BI "(struct cxlflash_cfg *cfg "  ","
.BI "struct ctx_info *ctxi "  ","
.BI "int *adap_fd "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cfg" 12
Internal structure associated with the host.
.IP "ctxi" 12
Context to release.
.IP "adap_fd" 12
Adapter file descriptor associated with new/recovered context.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Restablishes the state for a context-in-error.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -errno on failure
